Function to Read Sparse Matrix

Function readMatrix(Integer numRows, Integer numCols) 
    Integer numElements
    Print "Enter the number of non-zero elements:"
    Read numElements
    
    Array sparseMatrix[numElements] of SparseMatrixElement
    
    For i from 0 to numElements - 1 do
        Print "Enter row, column, and value for element", i + 1, ":"
        Read sparseMatrix[i].row
        Read sparseMatrix[i].col
        Read sparseMatrix[i].value
    End For
    
    Return sparseMatrix
End Function


Function to Print Sparse Matrix

Function printMatrix(Array sparseMatrix, Integer numElements) 
    Print "Sparse Matrix Representation:"
    For i from 0 to numElements - 1 do
        Print "Row:", sparseMatrix[i].row, "Column:", sparseMatrix[i].col, "Value:", sparseMatrix[i].value
    End For
End Function



Main Function

Function main()
    Integer numRows, numCols
    Print "Enter the number of rows and columns in the matrix:"
    Read numRows
    Read numCols
    
    Array sparseMatrix = readMatrix(numRows, numCols)
    Integer numElements = length of sparseMatrix
    
    printMatrix(sparseMatrix, numElements)
End Function





SparseMatrixElement Structure: This structure holds the row index, column index, and value of a non-zero element in the sparse matrix.

readMatrix Function: This function prompts the user to enter the number of non-zero elements and then reads the row, column, and value for each element, storing them in an array of SparseMatrixElement.

printMatrix Function: This function takes the array of sparse matrix elements and prints each non-zero element's row, column, and value.

main Function: This function initializes the process by reading the dimensions of the matrix, calling readMatrix to get the sparse matrix representation, and then calling printMatrix to display the results.
